Last updated: [24-09-2024]

Thank you for using PACSYS. We are committed to protecting your personal information and your right to privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how PACSYS collects, uses, and handles your information when you use our app.

1. Information We Collect

When you use PACSYS, we collect certain information to allow you to access the app's features. Specifically, we collect:

Email address

Display name


This information is collected when you sign in through Firebase authentication or Google Sign-In.

2. How We Collect Information

We collect your email address and display name when you log in through:

Firebase Authentication (authorized users only)

Google Sign-In


No other account information is collected from your Google or Firebase accounts.

3. How We Use Your Information

Your email address and display name are used for the following purpose:

To include your display name in the report file generated within the app.


We do not use your information for any other purpose.

4. Information Sharing and Disclosure

We do not share, sell, or rent your personal information to any third party. All information collected is solely used within the PACSYS app to provide its core functionality.

5. Data Security

We are committed to ensuring the security of your information. PACSYS does not share your information with third parties. Your data is protected through Firebase's security measures to prevent unauthorized access or disclosure.

6. Third-Party Services

PACSYS uses Firebase Authentication for user login. No other third-party services are integrated into the app.

7. Data Collection from Minors

PACSYS is not intended for use by individuals under the age of 18, and we do not knowingly collect personal information from minors.

8. Your Privacy Rights

If you have any questions or concerns about how your data is handled or if you wish to inquire about the data we collect, please contact us through the details below.

9. Contact Information

For privacy-related questions, please contact us at:

